data.description: Escape to the serenity of this magnificent 2.64-acre sunrise and sunset mountain view home, a sanctuary nestled amidst nature's beauty. This fully renovated home with 5 bedroom, 3 bath, 2 story home, this residence provides ample space for family and guests. The open floor plan seamlessly connects living, dining, and kitchen areas, creating an inviting atmosphere for hosting and entertaining guests. Deep kitchen sink with all natural wood cabinets. Large windows invite abundant natural light and showcase the view and cozy gas fireplace on each level. Master on main, plus additional bedroom and a flex room on main floor. Step outside to 2 expansive covered deck that offer the perfect vantage point for sunrise coffee or sunset cocktails. Walk-out basement level can serve as in-law suite with separate full kitchen and private entry. Enclosed outdoor patios on lower level, this outdoor spaces provide a seamless transition between indoor and outdoor living, allowing you to fully appreciate the mountain lifestyle. While nestled in nature, this mountain retreat is conveniently located to nearby towns and amenities. Additional features include the freedom to roam by having your own RV septic hookup on the property. Convenience meets functionality with three washer and dryer hookups. Adventure awaits right in your backyard with a 100-foot zip line and a short walk to the beautiful Lake, 'Hidden Lake' where you can enjoy a stroll and feed the ducks. Savor the fruits of nature with a variety of fruit-bearing trees on the property. Gather around the fire pit and create lasting memories under the starlit mountain sky. Two car garage enclosed and additional carport plus more than enough additional parking for guests. Watch the joy unfold as children and guests delight in the on-site playground, plus an outdoor shower in case you trail through the spring-fed creek or played in the watering hole. Don't miss the opportunity to make this mountain retreat your own. There is no HOA nor restrictions, and the land can be subdivided to build a separate income generating mountain property on the other end of the lot across natural spring - begin building generational wealth!
